This paper deals with the physical models and algorithmic applications of wireless networks, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves algebraic properties and approximation algorithms, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of SINR diagrams also involves partitioning the plane and proximity queries, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential role of SINR diagrams in the development of algorithms for wireless networks, which falls under the category of control and systems theory (cs.SY).
